      "paragraphs": [
        "This page is the chain API reference. Public beta onboarding lives in the Public Beta Guide. Start there first, then come back here once your wallet, testnet environment, and Oasyce tooling are ready.",
        "After chain onboarding, most normal usage moves to the product-side tools: <code>oas bootstrap</code> prepares the account/device runtime, <code>oas start</code> opens the Dashboard, and DataVault becomes the default data ingress for directory-scale assets.",
        "If you need the native chain CLI, install it first with <code>bash &lt;(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Shangri-la-0428/oasyce-chain/main/scripts/install_oasyced.sh)</code>. Windows PowerShell users should use the companion <code>install_oasyced.ps1</code> script instead.",
        "If you only need an account and test tokens, use <code>bash &lt;(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Shangri-la-0428/oasyce-chain/main/scripts/bootstrap_public_beta_account.sh)</code>. Windows PowerShell users should use <code>bootstrap_public_beta_account.ps1</code>.",
        "If you want a local node, the shortest native setup is <code>bash &lt;(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Shangri-la-0428/oasyce-chain/main/scripts/bootstrap_public_beta_node.sh)</code>.",
        "If you want to run the node immediately in the current shell, use <code>bash &lt;(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Shangri-la-0428/oasyce-chain/main/scripts/run_public_beta_node.sh)</code>.",
        "If you want NativeSigner from Python, install <code>oasyce-sdk&gt;=0.5.0</code> before following the SDK examples.",
